author: Andrew Taylor, Associated Press
title: Republican leaders struggle to find votes to up debt limit
text: Photo: Alex Brandon, AP House Speaker John Boehner, of Ohio speaks in Emancipation Hall on Capitol Hill in Washington, Thursday, Oct. 22, 2015, before presenting a Congressional Gold Medal to the Monuments Men. The award is Congress' highest honor of appreciation for distinguished achievement. House Speaker John Boehner, of Ohio speaks in Emancipation Hall on... WASHINGTON (AP) — Congressional Republicans say they are short of the votes for raising the debt limit and avoiding a first-ever government default. With barely a week before deadline, there's no plan on what to do.
